body:
There might be a cmake flag you can add when building onnxruntime binary:

./build.sh <bunch of build options> --cmake_extra_defines onnxruntime_DEBUG_NODE_INPUTS_OUTPUTS=1

(if you are using python, install the whl first.)

To dump the input or output for each op, add env variable when running your command
ORT_DEBUG_NODE_IO_DUMP_INPUT_DATA=1 ORT_DEBUG_NODE_IO_DUMP_OUTPUT_DATA=1 python test.py

I've used it for training, inference should go thru the same code path. You can try and see if it works for you.

code ref: onnxruntime/core/framework/debug_node_inputs_outputs_utils.cc
